WHO   — 1984 — a NOUTHESIA book-world
WHAT  — George Orwell · 1949 · the boot on the face, forever
WHERE — Nineteen Eighty-Four (George Orwell, 1949)  Framework inputs: Nineteen Eighty-Four (George Orwell, 1949)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — The last free act is to think two and two make four — guard it, because the Party's true aim was never your obedience but your belief.
HOW   — Winston Smith, a clerk at the Ministry of Truth who rewrites history for the Party, begins a forbidden diary and a forbidden affair with Julia, drawn toward the Brotherhood and the inner-Party man O'Brien. But O'Brien is the trap; arrested and tortured in the Ministry of Love, Winston is broken in Room 101 against his deepest fear, betrays Julia, and is remade — until he loves Big Brother.

